>>9ba27438-fe1b-498e-813b-8197307cbea9
Mar 30, 2020 Reddit 8kun board
https://archive.fo/wip/nW6Mo

Hey retards, here's the alt sites Anons are going to after 8koon shit the bed

If you're not in the know and still posting on 8kun, then let me shed some light. Despite the shitty rebranding of the site name to placate the media, the refusal to bring back /pol/ because of its baggage, and how slow everything still loads some of us still used the site. That was until the removal of a board from a BO despite the promise that boards would belong to them (yes, I'm talking about Mark) preluded the decision to ban all lolis on the site (using a shitty lawyer as an excuse because Jim wants to appeal to the QBoomers who hate lolis). Anyone who's not a redditchan refugee has jumped ship (mostly to fatchan but it got shutdown) and these are your options if you have half a brain (copied from the GG thread):

    /v/ on 8chan.moe (board owned by Mark) - alt domain 8chan.se, future alt domain 8chan.cc

Runs LynxChan. Currently having some technical problems/slowness because they're ironing out bugs and because their DDOS provider is moving CDN servers, but already works alright. Run by the /gamergatehq/ board owner with the aim of being a proper 8chan successor. Mark contributed funds but is not an administrator there, just a board owner for /v/.

    /vg/ on 8chan.moe (board owned by someone else) - alt domain 8chan.se, future alt domain 8chan.cc

This is the option if you think 8chan.moe is the site to use but don't want Mark as board owner.

    /v/ on julay.world

Runs LynxChan. Same host that shut down Fatchan, but maybe they'll be fine since they don't have a /pol/? Has a small existing userbase. Used to ban GG but doesn't anymore. Shutting down and relaunching with fewer boards in 3 months, but /v/ is meant to be one of those boards.

    /vg/ on smuglo.li

Runs Vichan. Same host that shut down Fatchan, but maybe they'll be fine since they don't have a /pol/? Run by /a/ mods who ban for things like bad grammar. Bans "political discussion" including GG and SJWs in videogames

    /videogames/ on 9chan.tw

Site is run by Josh, the owner of Kiwifarms, and runs Infinity Next. Site has bizarre rule about how loli can only be posted on dedicated boards without being posted alongside porn. They advertised on 4chan when they started.

Don't bitch at me for posting this on Reddit. It's obvious not everyone went on 8kun everyday and then came back wondering why there was so much bitching. Remember, 8kun is not 8chan and never was. It got rid of the two of the three biggest themes of 8chan, /pol/ and lolis. It's only there to appeal to QBoomers now.
